Proof that Thevening & Norton Equivalents Circuits are Equivalent






Note



The circuits are equivalent if they have the same \(i-v\) characteristics.



Thevenin
\[
\begin{gather}
V_L = V_T \frac{R_L}{R_T+R_L} \\
i_L = \frac{v_L}{R_L} = \frac{V_T}{R_T+R_L}
\end{gather}
\]


Norton
\[
\begin{gather}
i_L = i_N \frac{R_T}{R_N+R_L} \\
V_L = i_L R_L = I_N R_N \frac{R_L}{R_N+R_L} \\
i_N = \frac{V_T}{R_T} \\
V_L = V_T \frac{R_L}{R_T+R_L}
\end{gather}
\]
They are the same!

Solve Linear Set of Equations
\[
\begin{bmatrix}
R_1 + R_2 & -R_2 & 0 \\
-R_2 & R_2 + R_3 + R_4 & -R_4 \\
0 & -R_4 & R_4 + R_5 + R_6
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
i_A \\
i_B \\
i_C
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
v_s \\
0 \\
0
\end{bmatrix}
\]







Looks like Ohm’s Law!


\[
\begin{gather}
\bar{R} \bar{I} = \bar{V} \\
\bar{I} = \bar{R}^{-1} \bar{V}
\end{gather}
\]





